div.h1: Preemptive Timing: Timer Interrupt to Context Switch

div.p:
10ms Time Slice
Process A runs IRQ Scheduler Ctx Sw Process B runs ~9.995 ms ~1s ~2s ~2s ~9.995 ms
outb(0x43, 0x36) ; Mode 3 outb(0x40, 0x9B) ; Low byte outb(0x40, 0x2E) ; High byte
Time slice = 1 / frequency = 1 / 100 Hz = 0.01 seconds = 10 milliseconds
Each process gets 10ms before being preempted (if still READY)
Components: Register save: ~20 cycles CR3 reload: ~100-500 cycles Pipeline flush: ~10-20 cycles TLB effects: variable
context_switch: ; Save A's complete state mov [A->cpu.eax], eax mov [A->cpu.esp], esp mov [A->cpu.cr3], cr3

; Load B's complete state
mov cr3, [B->cpu.cr3] mov esp, [B->cpu.esp]
; Restore B's registers and iret iret
